---
import Layout from "@astro/layouts/Layout.astro";
import StaticHero from "@astro/components/StaticHero.astro";
---
<Layout title="AI Prompts for Language Learning — PromptAndGo" description="Use AI to learn Asian languages: Japanese, Korean, Mandarin, Thai, Vietnamese.">
  <StaticHero eyebrow="Language learning" title="Learn Asian languages with AI." subtitle="Conversation prompts, grammar explanations, and cultural context — for Japanese, Korean, Mandarin, Thai, Vietnamese, and more." />
  <section class="container max-w-3xl pb-16 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2>What works</h2>
    <p>Generic AI tutors miss the politeness and pragmatic layers that make Asian languages distinctive. Our prompts ask the AI to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Quiz you in the right register (formal/informal)</li>
      <li>Correct your honorifics, not just your grammar</li>
      <li>Explain why something sounds rude vs polite vs friendly</li>
      <li>Give cultural context for idioms and slang</li>
    </ul>
    <p><a href="/library">Browse language-learning prompts →</a></p>
  </section>
</Layout>
